Reasoning: The paper deals with decidability and characterization of regular forest languages definable in a fragment of first-order logic built from the descendant and sibling relations, which falls under the scope of logic (cs.LO) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of modalities for navigating trees also relates to formal language theory (cs.FL) and database theory (cs.DB). Finally, the mention of different horizontal modalities suggests a possible connection to programming languages (cs.PL).
